==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ecbatic
<hw>Ec*bat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Ecbasis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>Denoting a mere result
or consequence, as distinguished from <xex>telic</xex>, which denotes
intention or purpose; thus the phrase <grk>"i`na plhrw`qh</grk>, if
rendered ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>so that</xex> it was fulfilled,⟦rdquo⟧ is ecbatic;
if rendered ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>in order that</xex> it might be.⟦rdquo⟧ etc., is
telic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ecbole</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
